The paper deals with the problem of multi-robot routing on grids, which is a common problem in robotics (cs.RO). The algorithmic techniques used in the paper involve data structures (cs.DS), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and computational geometry (cs.CG). The paper also discusses the concept of solution time optimality, which is related to the field of swarm intelligence (cs.SI).
